column1: Have you found work on Quora?,https://qph.is.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-d58fba3a2a0a1511ecb76718f2381e71?convert_to_webp=true,Yes. I have received at least 6-7 interview invitations. Apart from that
column2:
.? a get a lot of these (almost once every week) :

"
column3: We are building a platform that will take the world by storm. It is a million dollar idea. Would you like to get on board ? We are looking for talented individuals like you who can handle the technical aspects. Good money is guaranteed&quot
column5:
.? I don't even bother replying to such messages. I have also noticed a meteoric rise in number of profile views and connection requests on LinkedIn ever since I started writing actively on Quora. I can recall at least 2 very genuine invitation from good startups offering me a role that I think might have suited me.

So yes
column6:
.? Quora might actually help you discover exciting career opportunities.

Edit : This answer was written on a positive note. I should add that I didn't accept any invitations. Moreover
column7: .? it was pretty evident from my LinkedIn and Quora profile that I am new grad fresh out of college who is actively seeking job opportunities. I do not think experienced developers will have much advantage from Quora - at least not at the time of writing this answer.,2016-05-20,08:59:41,
